Esser proposes to equate to extremism the insult of patriotic feelings
In order to legally protect the patriotic feelings of citizens from provocations and insults directed against Russia, Fair Russia proposes to equate the insult of patriotic feelings with extremist activity and to punish for this with five years in prison.
According to the newspaper "Izvestia", such amendments to the legislation, prepared by the Deputy Chairman of the Duma Committee on Energy Oleg Mikheev, have already been sent to obtain an opinion in the Supreme Court and the government.
