As Mikheev points out, in the domestic legislation there are sanctions for abuse of formal signs of state power - the flag and the coat of arms.
At the same time, according to the parliamentarian, the protection of Russians, whose feelings can be hurt by insulting state symbols and other manifestations of disrespect for our country, has not been sufficiently elaborated in Russian legislation.
As an example, he cites the discussions that unfold annually on the eve of Victory Day, when some media persons allow themselves to question the heroic feat of the people of the USSR in the fight against the Nazis.
On the eve of the main national holiday - Victory Day on May 9 - a real bacchanalia unfolds annually.
