The power engineers of Dnipropetrovsk region have launched a unique program to save the nests of storks
In ancient times, in order to bring the storks to the court, the peasants on a high pole installed a cart wheel, and the heavy nest held well on it.
Such special supports have not been put for a long time, so the storks chose the poles of power lines - the interwoven branches are based on wires, so that the aistine house stands reliably.
Grandmother Anya, near the house of which in the village of Ivanovka Petrikovsky district for twenty years lives a true family, began to notice how the nest settles, despite all the efforts of its inhabitants.
Birds put new twigs on top, and the bottom layer has already passed between the wires, is about to collapse.
Of course, it is a pity for the family of storks, who every year nested in the yard, brought out and fed for the summer three or four chicks, but I do not want to remain without light.
As soon as the birds flew to the warm edges, Anya's grandmother called the Tsarichansky RES, which owns the support.
I didn’t expect them to react so quickly.
When our specialists arrived in Ivanovka, they were surprised that the nest is still standing at all, - said the technical director of DTEK "Dneprooblenergo" Sergey Berezovsky.
On the wires, which were, in fact, already inside the nest, weighing 150 - 200 kilograms, corrosion began.
At any moment, the birds could have died from an electric discharge.
And local residents risked being left without light due to damage to the wires.
Therefore, linear fitters began the operation to save the nest, and not for the first time in our practice.
Helped ornithologists from the Dnepropetrovsk National University, who developed a scheme for the transfer of the nest.
They also conducted trainings for employees of district networks.
The famous Dnepropetrovsk ornithologist Alexander Ponomarenko advised power engineers at all stages of the reconstruction of nests.
To begin with, it was estimated that there are more than 50 truly “apartments” in the area in an emergency state.
For their reconstruction, special metal platforms resembling a funnel were welded.
The base was braided with willow branches, and then the old nest was moved there.
According to experts, it is enough to lay the old branches as a basis for the birds to recognize the nest and return to it.
Later, the storks will complete their own housing.
A month ago, the first nest was reconstructed in the village of Peschanka of the Novomoskovsk district.
Next to the electro-resistance put a new reinforced concrete pillar and placed on it a platform with an old, already inhabited nest.
The whole operation cost the power engineers nine thousand hryvnias.
And the other day the same housewarming took place in the village of Ivanovka Petrikovsky district in the yard of grandmother Ani.
Here, the platform was fixed in the same place, only raised above the wires.
Ornithologists are sure that cautious, conservative birds will not even notice in the spring that their "apartment" has undergone major repairs.
Until the end of the year, the same reconstruction expects four more nests in Pokrovsky and Tsarichansky districts of the Dnipropetrovsk region.
By the way, while some save rare birds, others mercilessly kill them.
The other day, the whole region flew around the sad news - in the village of Ust-Kamenka of the Apostolov district, on the day of the opening of the hunt for pheasants, poachers shot a swan family living on the local pond for entertainment.
The noble birds were not afraid of people at all - the locals fed them and did not hurt them.
When the villagers heard the shots, ran to the pond, four handsome swans were already lying dead on the water.
Now the staff of the Apostolovsky District Department of the police find out who shot at the birds listed in the Red Book.
