From October 28, the customs authorities of Russia began to apply additional measures to guarantee the delivery of goods, - said the Deputy head of the Eastern customs Vladimir Denisov.
The new model document is applicable in countries that have acceded to the Convention on International Carriage.
Checkpoints are working in enhanced mode.
The “FACTS” correspondent visited the border and talked with truckers who were hostages of the situation.
Prices in the roadside shop-cafe at the Novoazovsk checkpoint are growing every day, as is the queue from the trucks.
The trucks stand in several rows, stretching for about two kilometers.
Customs terminal Novoazovsk - Veselo-Voznesenka provides one of the most important transport routes from the south of Ukraine on the international highway.
From here, goods are sent to the Stavropol Territory of Russia, Kazakhstan, Georgia, Armenia.
Sunday before midnight was still allowed, and then introduced these rules, - complains trucker Alexei Golovanov (pictured), who carries goods from Turkey to Kazakhstan through Russia and has been spending almost a week in his car.
Under the new rules, to cross the border, I need an additional package of documents and payment for cargo insurance.
The amount depends on the cost of the cargo and the distance to which it is transported.
The minimum insurance is 4.5-5 thousand rubles (about 1100-1300 UAH).
Those who go near (say, to Georgia, Armenia) with a cargo worth up to 50 thousand dollars, pay somewhere 15 thousand rubles (3800 hryvnia) and pass.
And the rest are stuck - because no one has so much money with them!
Imagine if a driver carries a cargo worth only four thousand dollars, but all the way to Moscow, he needs 90 thousand rubles (almost 23 thousand hryvnias) to pay for transit!
Conditions for survival at the border - no, - complain truckers who settled down to eat near their cars.
In border shops and cafes and so always expensive, but such prices as here, we have not met anywhere!
The sellers oriented and quickly blew them: 15 hryvnia is a bar, seven hryvnia - a cup of coffee, 25 hryvnia - a plate of soup.
There's only one cafeteria.
And there's no toilet.
We sleep in the steppe, we go to the toilet there.
No washing, no shaving...
I can not get out of the car for a week, my wife prepared everything for me on the way.
A week will pass, - another trucker Viktor Skotarenko consoles himself.
Will my car be ready in a week?
Why do you have a liter and a half of water? - We are interested in the only border store.
There are 11 and 15 hryvnias.
Is the bottle crystal or is the water infused with silver?
We have a cafe, not a shop.
Take it while there is something else, - the saleswoman parries.
After the situation began to be covered in the media, the plight of Ukrainian drivers drew the attention of the authorities of the region.
The leadership of the Amvrosievsk and Novoazovsk regional state administrations have been instructed to provide drinking water to all those waiting in line at the Ukrainian-Russian border, said Sergei Dergunov, acting chairman of the Donetsk regional state administration.
Ambulance teams are currently on duty at checkpoints.
Also, for the convenience of people, bio-toilets will be installed.
According to the official, the problem associated with the queues will be solved in the coming days.
